  "body": "It is a well known issue in ie9/10 where pressing Enter on an input can trigger the click handler of an unrelated button somewhere else in the dom, if the button doesn't have a `type`.\n\nI was wondering if React should automatically add `type=\"button\"` when creating `button` elements if `type` isn't already in the props. Or should this be left to userland?\n\nCurrently I am monkey-patching `React.createElement` to automatically add the `type=\"button\"`:\n\n``` javascript\nReact.originalCreateElement = React.createElement;\nReact.createElement = function(type, _props, ...args) {\n  let props = _props;\n  if (type === 'button') {\n    if (!_props) {\n      props = { type: 'button' };\n    } else if (!_props.hasOwnProperty('type')) {\n      props = Object.assign({ type: 'button' }, _props);\n    }\n  }\n  return React.originalCreateElement(type, props, ...args);\n};\n```\n\nAlso wondering if there's a better way to do this.\n",
